The paper proposes an attention-based end-to-end model for multi-channel keyword spotting, which involves speech processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also involves natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of machine learning techniques suggests cs.LG (Learning), and the optimization of KWS results suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves transfer learning, which is a common technique in computer vision, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible category. However, since the focus of the paper is on speech processing and machine learning, cs.SD and cs.CL are the most likely categories.
